# Gitignored files to copy into worktrees Claude Code creates (--worktree,
# EnterWorktree, subagent worktrees, desktop sessions). Gitignore-syntax; only
# files that ALSO match .gitignore are copied (tracked files are never duped).
# Docs: https://code.claude.com/docs/en/worktrees#copy-gitignored-files-into-worktrees
#
# settings.local.json carries plugin enablement (enabledPlugins) AND the
# project permission allowlist. Without this line a fresh worktree starts with
# installed plugins OFF and prompts for permissions already granted on main.
# See skills/worktree/SKILL.md §2.
.claude/settings.local.json
# brand-foundry plugin: its own in-place repo (skills/brand-foundry/.git),
# gitignored so it stays out of the trunk. Listed here to copy it into new
# worktrees so the plugin is present. CAVEAT: a raw copy of a live nested .git is
# reliable only when the sub-repo is QUIESCENT — a concurrent commit during the
# copy corrupted it once (2026-06-20: `fatal: bad object HEAD`); if a worktree's
# copy is broken, re-clone it. See skills/nested-repos (chooser + the fragility).
skills/brand-foundry/
